  "text": "The Node.js ESM loader and CommonJS-ESM interop bridge is implemented across multiple JavaScript and C++ source files that work together to load, resolve, and evaluate ES modules while maintaining compatibility with the CommonJS loader.\n\n## Core ESM Loader Components\n\n### Primary Loader (lib/internal/modules/esm/loader.js)\nThe `ModuleLoader` class at line 110 serves as the central orchestrator for ESM loading. It manages module resolution caching, format detection, and the two-phase loading process (resolve and load hooks). The loader coordinates with translators and handles both standard and custom loader hooks.\n\n### Module Resolution (lib/internal/modules/esm/resolve.js)\nThe ESM specifier resolver provides the `defaultResolve` function that resolves module specifiers to absolute URLs. It handles package.json exports, conditions-based resolution, and relative/absolute path resolution. It works in conjunction with the CJS loader's package.json reader.\n\n### Module Job Pipeline (lib/internal/modules/esm/module_job.js)\nThe `ModuleJob` class (line 72) and `ModuleJobBase` (line 60) track the loading and linking/evaluation lifecycle of individual modules. `ModuleJobSync` (line 310) handles synchronous loading for require(ESM) scenarios. These classes manage:\n- Module instantiation and linking\n- Top-level await handling\n- Module dependency tracking\n- Error propagation\n\n### ESM Translators (lib/internal/modules/esm/translators.js)\nThe translators module provides format-specific module wrapping strategies:\n- `module` format: Standard ESM modules\n- `commonjs` format: CJS modules loaded via import()\n- `json` format: JSON files\n- `builtin` format: Node.js built-in modules\n- `wasm` format: WebAssembly modules\n- `module-typescript` and `commonjs-typescript`: TypeScript variants\n\nThe `createCJSModuleWrap` function at line 176 converts CommonJS modules into ESM-compatible ModuleWrap objects.\n\n### Load Phase (lib/internal/modules/esm/load.js)\nHandles the load hook chain, validates loader responses, and calls translators to generate module source code.\n\n### Format Detection (lib/internal/modules/esm/get_format.js and lib/internal/modules/esm/formats.js)\nDetermines module format based on:\n- File extension mappings (.mjs, .cjs, .json, .wasm)\n- Package.json \"type\" field\n- Content type headers for data: and file: protocols\n- Heuristic ESM syntax detection for ambiguous files\n\n### Loader Hooks (lib/internal/modules/esm/hooks.js)\nImplements the `HooksProxy` class that manages custom loader chains, validating hook return values and orchestrating the resolve/load two-phase process.\n\n### Supporting Components\n- **lib/internal/modules/esm/initialize_import_meta.js**: Initializes the import.meta object with url and resolve properties\n- **lib/internal/modules/esm/create_dynamic_module.js**: Creates synthetic modules for dynamic imports\n- **lib/internal/modules/esm/module_map.js**: Implements `ModuleMap`, `ResolveCache`, and `LoadCache` for caching module lookups and loaded modules\n- **lib/internal/modules/esm/utils.js**: Core utilities including `initializeESM()` and callback registration\n- **lib/internal/modules/esm/worker.js**: Runs custom loader hooks in a dedicated worker thread\n- **lib/internal/modules/esm/fetch_module.js**: Handles fetching module source code\n- **lib/internal/modules/esm/assert.js**: Validates import attributes\n- **lib/internal/modules/esm/shared_constants.js**: Defines constants shared between main and worker threads\n\n## CommonJS-ESM Interop Bridge\n\n### CJS Loader Integration (lib/internal/modules/cjs/loader.js)\nThe `finalizeEsmResolution` function at line 1258 bridges CJS and ESM resolution by:\n- Validating resolved module specifiers\n- Converting file URLs to paths\n- Checking file existence\n- Providing fallback error handling with CommonJS hints\n\nThe CJS loader also calls `loadESMFromCJS()` to handle scenarios where CommonJS code imports ESM modules.\n\n### Entry Point Detection (lib/internal/modules/run_main.js)\nDetermines at startup whether to use the ESM or CommonJS loader:\n- `executeUserEntryPoint()` at line 156 parses the main entry point\n- `shouldUseESMLoader()` at line 64 checks for:\n  - --experimental-default-type=module flag\n  - --experimental-loader flags\n  - --import preload modules\n  - File extensions (.mjs, .cts, .mts)\n  - package.json \"type\" field\n- `runEntryPointWithESMLoader()` at line 137 initializes the ESM loader and runs preload modules\n\n## Native C++ Bindings\n\n### ModuleWrap C++ Class (src/module_wrap.h and src/module_wrap.cc)\nThe `ModuleWrap` class wraps V8 Module objects:\n- **Constructor** (line 53 in .cc): Associates a JavaScript object with a V8 Module\n- **context()** method (line 87): Returns the creation context of the wrapped module\n- **GetHostDefinedOptions()** (line 144): Creates PrimitiveArray for host-defined options including module ID\n- **CompileSourceTextModule()**: Compiles source code into a V8 Module with caching support\n- **CheckUnsettledTopLevelAwait()** (line 106): Detects stalled top-level awaits at shutdown\n- **CreatePerContextProperties()**: Exposes ModuleWrap to JavaScript\n- **HostInitializeImportMetaObjectCallback()**: Initializes import.meta for each module\n\n### Binding Registration (src/node_binding.cc)\nThe module_wrap binding is registered in `NODE_BUILTIN_STANDARD_BINDINGS` at line 63, making it available via `internalBinding('module_wrap')`. This enables JavaScript code to:\n- Create ModuleWrap instances\n- Access module status constants (kEvaluating, kEvaluated, kUninstantiated)\n- Interact with V8 modules from JavaScript\n\n### Environment Integration (src/env.h and src/env.cc)\nThe Environment class maintains `hash_to_module_map` (line 772 in env.h) - a hash map from V8 Module identity hashes to ModuleWrap instances, enabling quick lookup of wrapped modules.\n\n## Execution Flow\n\nWhen Node.js starts:\n1. `executeUserEntryPoint()` determines if ESM or CJS should be used\n2. For ESM entry points, `runEntryPointWithESMLoader()` initializes the ModuleLoader\n3. The loader's `import()` method:\n   - Calls resolve hooks to get the URL and format\n   - Calls load hooks to get source code\n   - Uses translators to convert source to ESM ModuleWrap\n   - Creates a ModuleJob to link and evaluate the module\n4. ModuleJob manages linking of dependencies and evaluation with top-level await tracking\n5. For require(ESM), `finalizeEsmResolution()` bridges to ESM modules via the cascaded loader\n6. The C++ ModuleWrap binding provides the bridge between V8's Module API and JavaScript\n"
